For those of u following for the COVID19 updates- it is officially day 10 since I’ve returned from NY and I’m finally feeling relatively normal other than complete loss of my sense of smell and still some warmth in my chest occasionally but finally regaining energy to do things

For those of u following for the COVID19 updates- it is officially day 10 since I’ve returned from NY and I’m finally feeling relatively normal other than complete loss of my sense of smell and still some warmth in my chest occasionally but finally regaining energy to do things

If you are feeling even a little bit funny but don’t have a high enough fever or the right symptoms to get tested- just STAY HOME!!! Monitor yourself. Not only for your health but everyone else’s. I’m 22y/o and this is woopin me. Anyone & everyone is at risk- be smart!!

I’ve heard people saying some places are only testing if you have above a certain fever, but considering my temp never rose above 99.5F, I can attest that you can still be an active carrier without having a full fever or all the symptoms. It is so important to be aware of this!!!

My family suggested I come home, so I drove 5 hours to my parents’ house but stopped at a clinic nearby to get a test done. Though I didn’t have a fever anymore, they agreed to do the test since I had been in an extremely high-risk place for the past week and had a few symptoms

That was yesterday. Today I also feel pretty short of breath so I’m mainly staying in bed. Still extremely tired. Got the call today for my positive results, so I’m glad I have been keeping up with my symptoms day-to-day because I honestly didn’t think it would come back positive

The next day was a whoooole different story. Never felt exhaustion like this. You woulda thought I climbed Mount Everest the day before. I think I only got out of bed to go to the bathroom. Slept all day and felt super short of breath like I couldn’t get enough air in at once

Next day I had so much energy. I felt a lot better and thought maybe it was the end of all this. Still hadn’t gotten my results back, but I worked out in my room a little bit and cleaned up. However, I did feel a little short of breath. Figured it was from being lazy/sick lately

The headache wasn’t a normal headache but more like a hangover. If I moved my head too fast, coughed, or put my head upside down it felt like pounding in my head but sharp..so I just tried to stay put. I was also extremely fatigued so I didn’t mind staying in bed

The day after I had chills, dry cough, and low fever, I still had my dry cough and chills but it was now accompanied by a sore throat and lots of congestion. Couldn’t breathe out of my nose whatsoever but no longer had a fever. I also had this awful headache
